SEVEN PEOPLE ARE JAILED FOLLOWING KILLING OF GOSPORT MAN LEVI KENT

Hampshire and IoW News 

Seven people have been sentenced at Portsmouth Crown Court for their involvement in the murder of Levi Kent in Gosport.

Police were called to Keyes Road in Bridgemary at 2.32am on Friday 24 November 2023 where 22-year-old Levi had been assaulted by half-brothers Tommy and Aiden West. Levi‚Äôs injuries included six stab wounds inflicted by Tommy. Levi subsequently died from his injuries.

Tommy West, aged 18 of Fisgard Road in Gosport, was jailed for life with a minimum tariff of 21 years at Portsmouth Crown Court on Tuesday 15 October, having previously pleaded guilty to murder, robbery and possession of a bladed article.

Aiden West, aged 25, of Tudor Close in Gosport, was also jailed for life with a minimum tariff of 28 years yesterday. Aiden had previously pleaded guilty to robbery, however he denied charges of murder and possession of a bladed article and the case went to trial on Tuesday 25 June this year.

On Friday 16 August, Aiden West was convicted of murder, however he was found not guilty of possession of a bladed article in a public place.

Joining Aiden West in the dock during his trial were 43-year-old Peter West and 64-year-old Michael Figgins, both of whom were tried for two charges each of assisting an offender, which both denied. West and Figgins were both found guilty by the jury of one count each, relating to assisting Tommy West.

Peter West, of Wimpson Lane in Southampton, has now been sentenced to two years in prison.

Figgins, of St Ann‚Äôs Crescent in Gosport, is next due to appear in court on Monday 11 November.

As part of the investigation into Levi‚Äôs murder, led by Hampshire & Isle of Wight Constabulary‚Äôs Major Crime team, a further four people were charged with offences, which they all admitted at previous court hearings. The following individuals were sentenced for their involvement as follows:

Sarah Flynn, aged 36, of James Close in Gosport, sentenced to one year in prison today at Portsmouth Crown Court after pleading guilty to two counts of assisting an offender.

Joanne West, aged 45, of no fixed abode, sentenced to one year and three months after pleading guilty to two counts of assisting an offender.

Liam Savage, aged 38, of Trinity Green in Gosport, was sentenced to one year in prison after pleading guilty to two counts of assisting an offender.

Mark Phillips, aged 56, of Gilbert Close in Gosport, was sentenced to a suspended sentence of six months after pleading guilty to one count of perverting the course of justice.

In the lead up to Levi‚Äôs murder, on the evening of Thursday 23 November 2023, Aiden and Tommy West travelled to an address in James Close in a taxi paid for by Michael Figgins.

In the early hours of Friday, Tommy contacted Levi to arrange a drug deal, following which Tommy and Aiden both planned to rob Levi and take his drugs. 

Tommy and Aiden then left the address armed with knives, but the deal did not go ahead after Levi was spooked by their behaviour. A second deal was arranged, with Tommy and Aiden meeting Levi in Keyes Road where Tommy entered Levi‚Äôs car and stabbed him.

The attack caused Levi to accelerate the car which subsequently crashed into a wall on the opposite side of the road.

Levi exited the vehicle and ran, pursued by Tommy and Aiden. The prosecution case was that Tommy stabbed Levi several times ‚Äì including in the chest and right thigh. Aiden was present and involved in the assault. The knife used in the attack was then thrown onto the roof of the nearby medical centre, before the pair returned to James Close where Tommy changed his clothes. During this time, Sarah Flynn put some of Tommy‚Äôs clothing in the bin.

The court heard that afterwards Tommy and Aiden‚Äôs mother, Joanne West, paid for them to take a taxi to Liam Savage‚Äôs address in Trinity Green, and that the pair were laughing and joking during the journey.

Later that day, the attackers were picked up by Tommy‚Äôs dad Peter West and another man ‚Äì Michael Figgins ‚Äì and driven to various locations - enabling Tommy to discard some clothing at a friend‚Äôs address in the process.

Peter then drove Tommy to a police station at 5pm that evening so he could hand himself in. Aiden was arrested the next day.

The remaining suspects were arrested in the days that followed for their involvement in assisting Tommy and Aiden, and Mark Phillips was arrested after providing a false statement to police regarding the taxi booking Joanne West made for her sons.

Following the sentencing, which concluded on Wednesday 16 October, Levi‚Äôs family said: 
‚ÄúToday, we stand with heavy hearts as we reflect on the sentencing of the individuals responsible for the brutal murder of our beloved Levi. The court‚Äôs decision serves as a reminder of the profound loss we have endured.

‚ÄúOn the 24th November 2023, my son was cruelly taken from us in a cowardly act of violence that shattered our lives and our community. Levi was not just a victim, he was a son, a brother, an uncle, a grandson, a friend, and a source of joy for all who knew him. The pain of his loss has left an irreplaceable void in all of our lives, one that will never be filled.

‚ÄúWe remember him for his incredible ability to put a smile on everyone‚Äôs faces, his infectious laugh, his impressive dance moves, and his giant heart of pure gold.

‚ÄúDuring this painful chapter in our lives, we would like to express our gratitude to the police, the prosecution team, especially Mr Haggan and Mr Elton, and everyone involved in bringing these individuals to justice. Their commitment and dedication ensured that the truth prevailed, and we are thankful for their efforts during this horrific time.

‚ÄúOur family appreciates the love and support we have received from friends, family, and the community over these painful 11 months.

‚ÄúWhile today‚Äôs sentencing is supposed to bring a sense of closure, we know that we will remain forever incomplete as a family. We are broken, and the pain that we feel is immeasurable. Knife crime has devastating life long effects, it doesn‚Äôt just end one persons life, it ends the lives of all those that loved them too. 

‚ÄúWe will continue to honour Levis memory by cherishing the moments we shared with him, and by advocating for a safer community for everyone. 

‚ÄúThank you all for your support‚Äù.

Detective Chief Inspector Matt Gillooly, Senior Investigating Officer, said: ‚ÄúThis was a complex investigation which sought to unravel the network of individuals involved in Levi‚Äôs senseless murder ‚Äì ranging from the two people directly involved in the violent attack, to those who made efforts to assist the killers in evading capture, destroying evidence or seeking refuge.

‚ÄúWords can‚Äôt describe the irreversible pain caused to Levi‚Äôs family and friends as a result of his death, and our thoughts remain with them.

‚ÄúTommy & Aiden West ambushed and violently attacked Levi, leaving him to die in the street. Their cruelty is another shocking reminder of the tragedy born out of carrying knives.

‚ÄúBoth individuals will now spend a lengthy period of time in prison because of this, and their associates have also been rightly brought to justice.‚Äù

83-year-old Jessie Doolen Ward was found murdered in her home in Sasakwa, Oklahoma just days after Christmas on December 27th, 2011. Her murder remains open and unsolved. 

Jessie was found murdered in her living room at her home off State Hwy 56 outside of Sasakwa by a relative that evening. Jessie died from multiple gunshot wounds. There were no signs of forced entry or of a struggle. Jessie lived alone at the time and it's believed robbery could be the motive as her purse and two guns were taken from her home. Jessie had spoken to one of her granddaughters the morning of the murder and nothing seemed out of the ordinary at that time. 

Jessie was born on July 23rd, 1928 in Sasakwa where she lived her entire life. She attended Rocky Point and Sasakwa public schools growing up and went on to marry Troy Ward on June 7th, 1947 in Arkansas. They had two sons together. Their son Troy Ward died October 5th, 2011, just months before his mother, a double tragedy. Jessie's family continues to search for answers and justice in her murder. 

If you have any information on the murder of beloved grandmother, aunt, and mother Jessie Doolen Ward please call the OSBI at 800-522-8017. You can remain anonymous.

TWO YEAR OLD PUEBLO BOY CONFIRMED DEAD FROM FENTANYL - The Pueblo County Coroner has confirmed the first juvenile death of the year to fentanyl. A two year old boy was pronounced dead at the scene on September 23, and upon learning the cause of death, some relatives started blasting Facebook with ‚ÄúJustice for Ezikeal.‚Äù That information is now public and in the news. . 

His grandfather Jose Naranjo blasted a post on Facebook asking people to share it and called out for the media to cover the story. He said family members were told that Ezikeal had enough  Fentanyl in his system to possibly kill 2-3 adults. 

‚ÄúI think all who were involved or around, (including the mother, which he was in her care) the night of his death deserve to be charged and imprisoned for murder!‚Äù He blasted on FB. 

He continued: 

‚ÄúI HOPE THIS GOES VIRAL AND HITS THE NEWS SO HIS CASE AND SITUATION DOES NOT GO UNNOTICED OR PUSHED TO THE SIDE !!! PLEASE HELP AND SHARE !!!!! MUST COPY AND PASTE TO SHARE !!!!  #JUSTICEFOREZIKEAL #DRUGSKILL #CHILDABUSE #CHILDNEGLECT #MURDER.‚Äù

Police say they responded to a call on September 23 to a call that a child was unresponsive at a home. 

Police say they are still investigating the case, however, according to KOAA the District Attorney refused to comment and said the PPD hadn‚Äôt sent them an affidavit for criminal charges yet. Multiple inside sources, upon publishing this story messaged us saying that the mother and her friends were allegedly dealing drugs and that she had already lost custody of another child with a different father due to such activity and more. 

This is the 19th death so far in 2024, as reported by the coroner.
